    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\ni currently have two usecases need to get this value:\r\n* `setloclist(prevwin)`\r\n* `nvim_win_call(prevwin, nvim_win_set_config)`\r\n\r\nfor the first usecase, 0 can be used, and nvim will convert it to previous window internally.\r\nbut for the second, which is actually [a workaround for this issue](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/24129), i have no appropriate way to get the handle of prevwin, and `nvim_win_set_config` indicates the cursor is currently in a floating window, i dont want to use `wincmd p` x2 here as sometime floatwins will just be closed when them lost focus. (well of course, i can store the previous window when opening the floatwin for later use)\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nso i want an lua api to get the handle of previous window directly.\r\n\r\n--- updates\r\n(sorry, i mixed up 'last window' and 'previous window' here)",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
