            "body": "althought the proposal became more general, i still want to append the following approach for my initial usecase:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndo\r\n  local prevwin\r\n  vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"winleave\", { callback = function() prevwin = vim.api.nvim_get_current_win() end })\r\n  function vim.api.nvim_get_previous_win() return prevwin end\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nit is inspired by your last comment, i once thought this api can only be implemented by a `c` function, something like `return prevwin == NULL ? 0 : prevwin->handle;`.",
